    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Campbell</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 8, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If there is no direct communication with Vera Cruz, go to Havana and
                            there take English or French steamer for Vera Cruz. If you find it
                            occupied by republican forces, land there. If not, go to any United
                            States naval vessel there and ask the captain to land you at Casa Mata,
                            the headquarters of General Benavides, one mile from the city. The
                            Secretary of the Navy directs that the commander of the Tacony, or of
                            any United States vessel at Vera Cruz or its vicinity, render you all
                            necessary assistance.</p>
                <p>Mr. Romero advises this as your best course, and says you will probably
                            have no difficulty in going from there to the city of Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis D. Campbell,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., New Orleans.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
